  Am I running systemd?
    • The presence of `/run/systemd/system/` is allegedly the most reliable way to tell that debian is running systemd.
    • `readlink /sbin/init`

  Get list of services
    • `service --status-all` (SysVinit)
    • `ls → Linux/fhs/etc/init_d` (SysVinit)
    • `systemctl list-units --type=service`
    • `systemctl list-units --type=service --all` (show inactive services as well)

